      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WHATSTHETIMEMRWOLF (3) settled close enough but lacked the dash of the quinella horses when resuming over 800m at this track a fortnight ago. Strips fitter and is far more at home over today's trip. Not the strongest maiden so he gets his chance to break through. EGYPTIAN LASS (7) is a 13-start maiden back from a 14-week lay-off. At her best over five furlongs with three of her four placings coming at this trip. Has generally needed a couple of runs to hit her straps but in this thin field she is a major player. UNITE THE STARS (9) started favourite but struggled first-up in the mud at this track. Suited over a bit more ground today so watch for a much better performance. IMPENDING FORTUNE (1) resumes. Best form last prep was over further but while fresh he is not out of contention. Locally trained three-year-old DE LA SALLE (4) won a Grafton trial on 19 February and looks ready to make a bright start on debut.",
